Spring REST CORS Tutorial

  This tutorial demonstrates two ways to configure Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) for
  OfficeFloor REST endpoints declared as YAML files:

   * <<Composition-level CORS>> — declared in the YAML file under <<<composition: cors:>>>, applies to
     all HTTP methods served by that endpoint file

   * <<Annotation-level CORS>> — <<<@CrossOrigin>>> placed on the service class, picked up automatically
     by OfficeFloor at start-up

  {{{https://github.com/officefloor/OfficeFloor/tree/master/tutorials/springboot/SpringRestCorsHttpServer}Tutorial Source}}



